OL,7,FMrs Nonweiler, 74, who is chair of the
OL,8,FReading Reform Foundation, has trained
OL,9,Fteachers, and advised governments
OL,10,Faround the world on evidence-based
OL,11,Fmethods of teaching reading.
OL,13,FShe says the Welsh Government must act
OL,14,F"very urgently" by scrapping its new
OL,15,F"flawed" literacy centre in Bangor and
OL,16,Fdirect the money to schools for
OL,17,Fevidence-based teaching.
OL,19,FOtherwise, she warns, "Wales will
OL,20,Fcontinue to fail those who need
OL,21,Fsupport the most."
