OL,7,FShe argues this means the "mixed
OL,8,Fmessages" that paralysed the panel are
OL,9,Fnow being written into policy.
OL,11,F"A programme and resources will be
OL,12,Foffered free to schools, funded by
OL,13,Ftaxpayers," she wrote in an open
OL,14,Fletter to Lynne Neagle. "But they will
OL,15,Fnot be fit for purpose."
OL,17,FInstead, she calls for the panel to be
OL,18,Fdisbanded, the new programme scrapped,
OL,19,Fand the money redirected straight to
OL,20,Fschools.
