OL,7,FIn PIRLS 2021, which measures younger
OL,8,Fpupils reading skills, England ranked
OL,9,F4th of 43 countries; Wales did not
OL,10,Ftake part but has committed to joining
OL,11,Fthe next round.
OL,13,FThe schools' watchdog Estyn has
OL,14,Festimated that up to 30% of children
OL,15,Fleave primary schools unable to use
OL,16,Fbasic reading skills well.
OL,18,F"Why should children in Wales have
OL,19,Fless chance of becoming literate than
OL,20,Fchildren in England?" Mrs Nonweiler
OL,21,Fasked.
