OL,7,FEngland's turnaround in reading began
OL,8,Fwhen phonics became mandatory in all
OL,9,Fstate schools.
OL,11,FTeachers were trained to follow a
OL,12,Fsystematic programme of synthetic
OL,13,Fphonics, which was backed by
OL,14,Fgovernment guidance and Ofsted
OL,15,Finspection criteria.
OL,17,FProponents say results were visible
OL,18,Fwithin a decade: in PIRLS 2021,
OL,19,FEnglish ten-year-olds achieved one of
OL,20,Fthe highest literacy scores in the
OL,21,Fworld.
