OL,7,FThere are concerns that Wales' new
OL,8,Fcurriculum exacerbates its literacy
OL,9,Fproblems, as fluent reading depends
OL,10,Fnot only on decoding words but also on
OL,11,Funderstanding and inference.
OL,13,FEvidence shows that one of the most
OL,14,Fimportant factors in the development
OL,15,Fof reading comprehension is a child's
OL,16,Fbackground knowledge. The more
OL,17,Fknowledge children have of a
OL,18,Fparticular subject, the better their
OL,19,Freading comprehension.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G25/28
